.\"
.TH "startMaintenanceMode" "1" "" "SequoiaDB User Manuals" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
startMaintenanceMode \- start Maintenance mode in the cluster
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]SdbDC.startMaintenanceMode(<options>)\f[]
.SH CATEGORY
.PP
SdbDC
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This function is used to start the Maintenance mode for nodes in specified
replica groups within the cluster.
The nodes in Maintenance mode do not participate in replica group elections as
well as the calculation of replSize.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[]
.PP
Cannot set Maintenance mode for all nodes in a replica group.
.RE
.SH PARAMETERS
.PP
options ( \f[I]object, required\f[] )
.PP
Specify the Maintenance mode attributes through the parameter "options":
.IP \[bu] 2
HostName ( \f[I]string\f[] ): The effective host for Maintenance mode (mutually
exclusive with Location)
.RS 2
.PP
The specified hostname needs to exist in the current replica group, and all
nodes on this host will start Maintenance mode.
.PP
Format: \f[C]HostName: "sdbserver"\f[]
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[]
.PP
The primary node of catalog replica group (Catalog primary node) cannot start
Maintenance mode unless using the Enforced parameter.
.RE
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
Location ( \f[I]string\f[] ): The effective location for Maintenance mode
(mutually exclusive with HostName)
.RS 2
.PP
The specified location needs to exist in the current cluster, and all nodes in
replica groups within this location will start Maintenance mode.
.PP
Format: \f[C]Location: "GuangZhou"\f[]
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
MinKeepTime ( \f[I]number, required\f[] ): Minimum keep time for Maintenance
mode.
The value range is [1, 10080], and the unit is minutes.
.RS 2
.PP
Format: \f[C]MinKeepTime: 100\f[]
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
MaxKeepTime ( \f[I]number, required\f[] ): Maximum keep time for Maintenance
mode.
The value range is [1, 10080], and the unit is minutes.
.RS 2
.IP \[bu] 2
MaxKeepTime must be greater than or equal to MinKeepTime
.IP \[bu] 2
The system will automatically stop Maintenance mode when MaxKeepTime is reached
.PP
Format: \f[C]MaxKeepTime: 200\f[]
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
Enforced ( \f[I]boolean\f[] ): Whether to force start Maintenance mode, default
is false.
.RS 2
.IP \[bu] 2
When set to true, allows starting Maintenance mode for catalog replica group
primary nodes
.IP \[bu] 2
Special attention should be paid to system availability impact in forced mode
.PP
Format: \f[C]Enforced: true\f[]
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
Domain ( \f[I]string | string array\f[] ): Filter by domain, only operate on
data groups belonging to the specified domain(s).
A single domain name or an array of domain names can be specified
.RS 2
.PP
Format: \f[C]Domain: "mydomain"\f[] or
\f[C]Domain: ["domain1", "domain2"]\f[]
.RE
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[]
.PP
When the replica group has a primary node, the primary node will not be changed.
About time parameters: \- Both MinKeepTime and MaxKeepTime are required
parameters \- MinKeepTime value should be less than or equal to MaxKeepTime \-
After successfully starting Maintenance mode, nodes will remain in Maintenance
mode until MinKeepTime is reached \- During the MinKeepTime\-MaxKeepTime period,
if node status is normal, Maintenance mode will be automatically released \-
After MaxKeepTime expires, nodes will forcibly exit Maintenance mode
.RE
